                            <comment id="31934" author="adilger" created="Thu, 22 Mar 2012 20:31:06 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The llmount fix is only really in the test scripts and do not fix this problem for users at all. I think that we should make the proc tunable more forgiving - arriving it to the minimal value if a value lower than this is used, and the maximum if a value higher than this is used. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;At that point it makes sense to also remove the workarounds in the test scripts. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="31845" author="johann" created="Thu, 22 Mar 2012 05:35:43 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I think the llmount issue has been fixed in this ticket in &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-958&quot; title=&quot;tests: debug_mb set incorrectly for smp or vm&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-958&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-958&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="31844" author="freysteinn" created="Thu, 22 Mar 2012 05:28:48 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This machine has one E5603 CPU with 4 cores.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="31842" author="freysteinn" created="Thu, 22 Mar 2012 05:25:45 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;It seems that I need to have lctl set_param debug_mb=24 for this to work.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;When I ran /usr/lib64/lustre/tests/llmount.sh it automatically tried to use debug_mb=10, that is why it became a problem.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
